(Harper's Bike Hire - Frequently Asked Questions \(2026\)) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Where are you?) Tj T*
(Unit 4, Riverside Yard, Ashford Lane, Marlow SL7 1DD - two minutes) Tj T*
(from the Thames Path. Free customer parking on site.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(What are your opening hours?) Tj T*
(April to September: 9am to 6pm, seven days a week.) Tj T*
(October to March: 9am to 4:30pm, closed Mondays.) Tj T*
(Last hire leaves 2 hours before closing.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Do I need to book in advance?) Tj T*
(Weekends and school holidays usually sell out, so booking ahead is) Tj T*
(strongly recommended. Midweek walk-ins are normally fine.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Is there a minimum age?) Tj T*
(Riders must be 14 or over to hire their own bike. Under-14s ride) Tj T*
(child bikes booked by an accompanying adult. E-bike riders must be) Tj T*
(18 or over with photo ID.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Are helmets included?) Tj T*
(Yes - every hire includes a helmet, lock and puncture repair kit at) Tj T*
(no extra charge. You are welcome to bring your own helmet.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Can you suggest routes?) Tj T*
(Yes. We keep free laminated route cards for three loops: the 12 km) Tj T*
(family towpath loop, the 28 km Chilterns gravel loop, and the 45 km) Tj T*
(road circuit. Staff will happily mark up quieter alternatives.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(What if I get a puncture or breakdown?) Tj T*
(Every bike carries a repair kit. If you cannot fix it, call the) Tj T*
(shop - within 10 km we come to you free of charge during opening) Tj T*
(hours; beyond that a £15 recovery fee applies.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Can I take the bikes on the train?) Tj T*
(Standard bikes, yes \(subject to the operator's cycle policy\).) Tj T*
(E-bikes are not permitted on rail replacement buses.) Tj T*
ET
